To determine the winning situation in a Tic Tac Toe game with JavaScript code, you can use the following approach:

1. Create an array that represents the game board, with each element initialized to null, indicating an empty square.

```javascript
var board = [null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null];
```

2. Create a function that checks for a winning situation by looping through all possible win combinations and checking if the board has those combinations.

```javascript
function checkWin(board, player) {
  // Check rows for a win
  if ((board[0] === player && board[1] === player && board[2] === player) ||
      (board[3] === player && board[4] === player && board[5] === player) ||
      (board[6] === player && board[7] === player && board[8] === player)) {
    return true;
  }

  // Check columns for a win
  if ((board[0] === player && board[3] === player && board[6] === player) ||
      (board[1] === player && board[4] === player && board[7] === player) ||
      (board[2] === player && board[5] === player && board[8] === player)) {
    return true;
  }

  // Check diagonals for a win
  if ((board[0] === player && board[4] === player && board[8] === player) ||
      (board[2] === player && board[4] === player && board[6] === player)) {
    return true;
  }

  // No win found
  return false;
}
```

3. Call the checkWin function after each player move and check if the current player has won.

```javascript
if (checkWin(board, 'X')) {
  console.log('X has won');
} else if (checkWin(board, 'O')) {
  console.log('O has won');
}
```

This approach should allow you to determine the winning situation in a Tic Tac Toe game using JavaScript code.

